goals.question: What is the distribution of airports by country?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of number of airports by country
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand which countries have the most and least number of airports. It can also help us identify any outliers or countries with significantly higher or lower number of airports compared to others.

goals.question: What is the distribution of airports by type?
goals.visualization: Pie chart of number of airports by type
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the proportion of different types of airports in the dataset. It can also help us identify any dominant types of airports.

goals.question: What is the distribution of airports by elevation?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of airport elevations. It can also help us identify any outliers or airports with significantly higher or lower elevations compared to others.

goals.question: What is the distribution of airports by latitude and longitude?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of airport latitude and longitude
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of airports across the world. It can also help us identify any clusters or patterns in the distribution.

goals.question: What is the distribution of airports by runway length?
goals.visualization: Box plot of airport runway length
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of airport runway lengths. It can also help us identify any outliers or airports with significantly longer or shorter runways compared to others.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    country_counts = data['country'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=country_counts.index, y=country_counts.values, palette='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend(title='Countries', loc='upper right', labels=country_counts.index)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    airport_counts = data['type'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(airport_counts, labels=airport_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by type?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(airport_counts.index, loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.3, 1))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='elevation', bins=30, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['elevation'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['elevation'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of airports by elevation?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Elevation")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Airports")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    sns.boxplot(x=data['runway_length'], ax=ax)
    median_runway_length = data['runway_length'].median()
    ax.axvline(median_runway_length, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_runway_length:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Runway Length')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by runway length?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
